{"review": [{"text_id": "BJe2djKE3X", "sid": 0, "sentence": "The authors propose a method for image restoration, where the restored image is the MAP estimate."}, {"text_id": "BJe2djKE3X", "sid": 1, "sentence": "A pretrained GAN is utilized to approximate the prior distribution of the noise-free images."}, {"text_id": "BJe2djKE3X", "sid": 2, "sentence": "Then, the likelihood induces a constraint which is based on the degradation function."}, {"text_id": "BJe2djKE3X", "sid": 3, "sentence": "In particular, the method tries to find the latent point for which the GAN generates the image, which if gets degraded will match the given degraded image."}, {"text_id": "BJe2djKE3X", "sid": 4, "sentence": "Also, an optimization algorithm is presented that solves the proposed constrained optimization problem."}, {"text_id": "BJe2djKE3X", "sid": 5, "sentence": "I find the paper very well written and easy to follow."}, {"text_id": "BJe2djKE3X", "sid": 6, "sentence": "Also, the idea is pretty clean, and the derivations are simple and clear."}, {"text_id": "BJe2djKE3X", "sid": 7, "sentence": "Additionally, the Figures 2,3 are very intuitive and nicely explain the theory."}, {"text_id": "BJe2djKE3X", "sid": 8, "sentence": "However, I think that there are some weaknesses (see comments):"}, {"text_id": "BJe2djKE3X", "sid": 9, "sentence": "Comments:"}, {"text_id": "BJe2djKE3X", "sid": 10, "sentence": "#1) I do not understand exactly what the \"general method\" means. Does it mean that you propose a method, where you can just change the F, such that to solve a different degradation problem? So you provide the general framework where somebody has to specify only the F?"}, {"text_id": "BJe2djKE3X", "sid": 11, "sentence": "#2) Clearly, the efficiency of the method is highly based on the ability of the GAN to approximate well the prior distribution of the noise-free images."}, {"text_id": "BJe2djKE3X", "sid": 12, "sentence": "#3) There are several Equations that can be combined, such that to save enough white space in order to discuss further some actual technical details."}, {"text_id": "BJe2djKE3X", "sid": 13, "sentence": "For instance, Eq. 2,3 can be easily combined using the proportional symbol, Eq. 8,9,10,11 show actually the same thing."}, {"text_id": "BJe2djKE3X", "sid": 14, "sentence": "#4) I think that the function F has to be differentiable, and this should be mentioned in the text."}, {"text_id": "BJe2djKE3X", "sid": 15, "sentence": "Also, I believe that some actual (analytic) examples of F should be provided, at least  in the experiments."}, {"text_id": "BJe2djKE3X", "sid": 16, "sentence": "The same holds for the p(Omega)."}, {"text_id": "BJe2djKE3X", "sid": 17, "sentence": "This parameter Omega is estimated individually for each degraded image?"}, {"text_id": "BJe2djKE3X", "sid": 18, "sentence": "#5) Before Eq. 8 the matrix V is a function of z and should be presented as such in the equations."}, {"text_id": "BJe2djKE3X", "sid": 19, "sentence": "#6) I believe that it would be nice to include a magnified image of Fig. 3, where the gradient steps are shown."}, {"text_id": "BJe2djKE3X", "sid": 20, "sentence": "Also, my understanding is that the optimization goal is to find first a feasible solution, and then find the point that maximizes f. I think that this can be clarified in the text."}, {"text_id": "BJe2djKE3X", "sid": 21, "sentence": "#7) The optimization steps seem to be intuitive, however, there is not any actual proof of converge."}, {"text_id": "BJe2djKE3X", "sid": 22, "sentence": "Of course, the example in the Figure 3 is very nice and intuitive, but it is also rather simple."}, {"text_id": "BJe2djKE3X", "sid": 23, "sentence": "I would suggest, at least, to include some empirical evidences in the experiments that show convergence."}, {"text_id": "BJe2djKE3X", "sid": 24, "sentence": "#8) In the experiments I think that at least one example of F and p(Omega) should be presented."}, {"text_id": "BJe2djKE3X", "sid": 25, "sentence": "Also, what the numbers in Table 4 show? Which is the best value that can be achieved?"}, {"text_id": "BJe2djKE3X", "sid": 26, "sentence": "These numbers correspond to several images, or to a unique image?"}, {"text_id": "BJe2djKE3X", "sid": 27, "sentence": "#9) I think that MNIST is almost a toy experiment, since the crucial component of the proposed method is the prior modeling with the GAN."}, {"text_id": "BJe2djKE3X", "sid": 28, "sentence": "I believe that a more challenging experiment should be conducted e.g. using celebA dataset."}, {"text_id": "BJe2djKE3X", "sid": 29, "sentence": "Minor comments:"}, {"text_id": "BJe2djKE3X", "sid": 30, "sentence": "#1) In the paragraph after Eq. 4 the equality p_r(x)=p_G(x) is very strong assumption."}, {"text_id": "BJe2djKE3X", "sid": 31, "sentence": "I would suggest to use the \\simeq symbol instead."}, {"text_id": "BJe2djKE3X", "sid": 32, "sentence": "#2) After Eq. 6 the \"nonnegative\" should be \"nonzero\"."}, {"text_id": "BJe2djKE3X", "sid": 33, "sentence": "#3) Additional density estimation models can be used e.g. VAEs, GMM."}, {"text_id": "BJe2djKE3X", "sid": 34, "sentence": "Especially, I believe that the VAE will provide a way to approximate the prior easier than the GAN."}, {"text_id": "BJe2djKE3X", "sid": 35, "sentence": "#4) In Section 2 paragraph 2, the sentence \"However, they only ... and directly\" is not clear what means."}, {"text_id": "BJe2djKE3X", "sid": 36, "sentence": "In general, I find both the proposed model and optimization algorithm interesting."}, {"text_id": "BJe2djKE3X", "sid": 37, "sentence": "Additionally, the idea is nicely presented in the paper."}, {"text_id": "BJe2djKE3X", "sid": 38, "sentence": "Most of my comments are improvements which can be easily included."}, {"text_id": "BJe2djKE3X", "sid": 39, "sentence": "The two things that make me more skeptical, is the convergence of the proposed algorithm and the experiments."}, {"text_id": "BJe2djKE3X", "sid": 40, "sentence": "The MNIST is a relatively simple experiment, and I would like to see how the method works in more challenging problems."}, {"text_id": "BJe2djKE3X", "sid": 41, "sentence": "Also, I think that additional methods to compute the image prior should be included in the experiments."}], "reviewlabels": [{"text_id": "BJe2djKE3X", "sid": 0, "labels": {"coarse": "Structuring", "fine": "Structuring.Summary", "asp": "", "pol": ""}, "secondarylabels": [], "merge-with-prior": false}, {"text_id": "BJe2djKE3X", "sid": 1, "labels": {"coarse": "Structuring", "fine": "Structuring.Summary", "asp": "", "pol": ""}, "secondarylabels": [], "merge-with-prior": false}, {"text_id": "BJe2djKE3X", "sid": 2, "labels": {"coarse": "Structuring", "fine": "Structuring.Summary", "asp": "", "pol": ""}, "secondarylabels": [], "merge-with-prior": false}, {"text_id": "BJe2djKE3X", "sid": 3, "labels": {"coarse": "Structuring", "fine": "Structuring.Summary", "asp": "", "pol": ""}, "secondarylabels": [], "merge-with-prior": false}, {"text_id": "BJe2djKE3X", "sid": 4, "labels": {"coarse": "Evaluative", "fine": "Evaluative", "asp": "Soundness/Correctness", "pol": "P-Positive"}, "secondarylabels": [], "merge-with-prior": false}, {"text_id": "BJe2djKE3X", "sid": 5, "labels": {"coarse": "Evaluative", "fine": "Evaluative", "asp": "Clarity", "pol": "P-Positive"}, "secondarylabels": [], "merge-with-prior": false}, {"text_id": "BJe2djKE3X", "sid": 6, "labels": {"coarse": "Evaluative", "fine": "Evaluative", "asp": "Clarity", "pol": "P-Positive"}, "secondarylabels": [], "merge-with-prior": false}, {"text_id": "BJe2djKE3X", "sid": 7, "labels": {"coarse": "Evaluative", "fine": "Evaluative", "asp": "Clarity", "pol": "P-Positive"}, "secondarylabels": [], "merge-with-prior": false}, {"text_id": "BJe2djKE3X", "sid": 8, "labels": {"coarse": "Structuring", "fine": "Structuring.Heading", "asp": "", "pol": ""}, "secondarylabels": [], "merge-with-prior": false}, {"text_id": "BJe2djKE3X", "sid": 9, "labels": {"coarse": "Structuring", "fine": "Structu